An Act allowing “print-free” digital legal notices for the town of Wellesley.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Purpose.
2 In light of the lack of an available adequate print newspaper in the town of Wellesley, the
3 purpose of this act is to allow the town of Wellesley, including the Select Board, the School
4 Committee, the Planning Board, and all other elected or appointed boards and committees, or
5 municipal officials, to satisfy legal notice requirements entirely by digital publications.
6 SECTION 2. Process.
7 Where legal notice in a newspaper or a newspaper of general circulation is required by
8 statute, bylaw, or judicial order, alternative means of posting such notice, as specified in section
9 3 of this Act, may be used if approved by a majority vote of the public body or at the discretion
10 of the municipal official legally required to post such notice.
11 SECTION 3. Means of Legal Notice Publication.
1 of 2

12 Notwithstanding section 13(b) of chapter 4 of the General Laws, and subject to section 2
13 of this Act, whenever legal notice in a newspaper or newspaper of general circulation is required
14 by statute, bylaw, or judicial order, such notice requirement shall be satisfied by posting notice in
15 one or more of the following places:
16 (A) A print newspaper of local or general circulation;
17 (B) A newspaper’s website;
18 (C) Websites reporting local news and opinion which satisfy the criteria for digital
19 publication as set forth in said section 13(b) of said chapter 4;
20 (D) A statewide website that may be maintained as a repository for such notices; or
21 (E) A townwide website that may be maintained as a repository for such notices.
22 SECTION 4. Legal Requirements.
23 Nothing set forth in this Act shall be construed to alter or amend the timing requirements
24 of the publication of legal notices set forth in statute, bylaw, or judicial order.
25 SECTION 5. This act shall take effect upon its passage.
